text:
안무 진심 미친 거 같애... 특히 중간에 있는 사람이 이끄는 듯한 안무가 너무 최고임... 가운데에선 안무를 간단히 하는데 주변에서 화려하게 움직이는 게 진심 멋있는 거 같음 연쇄적으로 움직이는 것도 너무 완벽해서 볼 때마다 쾌감 느껴지고... 세븐틴 다른 노래 안무들도 이런 포인트들이 들어있는데 아무래도 안무 짜는 사람이 같으니 멤버 취향이 반영되는 거 같음 근데 노래 이해도 높은 사람이 춤을 짜니까 더더욱 춤=노래 일치가 되는 것 같음... 춤만 봐도 노래가 들리는 느낌?

좋아하는 안무 몇개만 뽑자면... 여긴 안 좋아할 수가 없는 부분ㅋㅋ(1:23) 꽃을 형상화한 안무도 정말 최고임 (1:56-2:02) 여긴 완전 영화같아서 좋음(2:37) 여긴 모든 안무중에 제~일 좋아하는 부분 노래에서도 제일 감동적인 부분인데 춤도 감동적임... =최고 (3:21) 사실 내 최애 안무 책갈피 만들려고 빌드업함ㅋ

author: @habersmashery
text:
This is amazing. It’s such an expressive choreo and I love how they change the levels (sitting, crouching, standing etc) to smoothly bring different vocalists in and out of the lead role, and then swallow them back into the group again.
And how the chorus choreo changes - unified for the first round, staggered in the second, and then unified again but facing different directions in the third. It makes it feel fresh each time.
And for 13 people!

author: @bex3577
text:
alright so im not a carat (yet but i probs will be in a weeks time) but i just wanna say. this choreo and song is so beautiful that im crying. like, i dont really know whos these boys are but the emotion in their voice and the way they dance is absolutely beautiful. i dont know if this is right or if im just understanding it wrong, but from the way i see it, this song is literally just them saying we dont have the words to say thank you to our fans, there isnt a word strong enough, so thank you will have to do. 

also? the fact that hoshi (i think thats who everyone is saying choreographed it, correct me if im wrong) incorporated sign language and the formation of thx during the bridge? thats so unique and incredible and just beautiful and meaningful and im literally just sitting here in awe of this song. 

anyways, ive listened to quite a few of their songs since discovering these guys a few days ago, and their all incredible. that being said, i dont think anything will beat this one for me, it makes me cry in the best way.

author: @valeryaleman8084
text:
Anyone know if Junhui practiced ballet, contemporary dance or something besides piano, wushu and things like that *BECAUSE THE ESTHETICS OF THE MOVEMENTS OF THAT BOY IS INCREDIBLE* stop the video exactly in the 1:10 minute see his arms, his legs outstretched, his shoulders and the extension of his neck just  WOW


and let's talk about the "thanks" MV, the part in which he is dancing alone in a kind of cafeteria the fall in that "fourth position" in a beautiful way and the slip he makes afterwards to get to the "souplesse", it is SUBTLE AND PRECIOUS IT IS SIMPLY ART OMG

All svt dances incredibly well and I say with confidence that you can't choose a "main dancer" because they are all incredibly good, I dare say that they are the group of guys with the best dancers and choreography that the kpop industry has right now. But many times I can't stop seeing Junhui because seriously something different and special is technically seen in all the dances that makes him attractive to the eye (artistically speaking) the way his arms and legs move , their expressions, their shoulders, their neck, EVERYTHING *(look at the beautiful fourth position that he does in the minute **3:33**)* and I say this with experience I'm professional dancer and I've seen so many dancer in along time and he's so special and artistical, he's a masterpiece

author: @asyrdal4059
text:
Okay, I'm not even a carat (let's say YET because the way things are going that could quickly change) but this song is amazing? And I've seen some pretty amazing KPOP choreos in my short 8 or so months as a KPOP fan but this one really takes the cake.
Let me make sure I've got this straight--
- It was choreographed by a member
- FOR 13 PEOPLE BTW
- It includes freaking sign language
- AND spells words?
- And somehow it didn't win choreo of the year? 
Dude.
I don't care who you stan, be it BTS or TXT, Blackpink or TWICE, in my opinion you'd have to be blind to see this choreography isn't a gift.

(In case anyone is curious, I'm a MOA/ARMY (usually MOARMY) that just joined kpop after the BBMA's 2019. This song in particular from Seventeen caught my eye, and I'm slowly falling in love. <3)

author: @crystal110698
text: I really like this choreography... Besides the sign language of "thank you" and the pinky promise thing, i just realised at 1:22 and 2:26, if you were to look carefully or have a camera above them, the formation spells out THX (i just realised it thanks to one of the comments). I remember crying and getting goosebumps when i first heard the song as i watched the MV when they released it. I was so touched by the lyrics and so awed by the melody. I remember feeling very thankful and proud to have them as my idols, because they always have their fans in mind... I think i should be thanking them more than them thanking me lol. It been 3 years and a little over 6 months since i started loving and supporting them, and still, i always cry when they play the "to carats" VCR during concerts... I go for the ones in my country of course, but the VCRs never fail to make me cry because they are always thinking about us so i feel loved and touched...(people around me would stare at me or tell me not to cry lol) I just love them so much... They'll always have a special place in my heart!

author: @bella7962
text:
The choreographer for THANKS said that if you look at the choreography line during DK's part at 1:22 and 2:26, the formation shifts to spell out T H X.

He said that people must have probably missed it because they were focused on the sign language aspect of the choreography.

If you think that you can't love Seventeen any more than you already did well think again because I fell in love with them all over again after realizing that not only did they used sign language to say thank you, they spelled it out for us in their choreography too.

text:
This choreo is everything. I'm an ARMY and this is my first Seventeen dance practice video (and this is the only song I've heard) and I always had Fire and BS&T up in that position but OMG! THIS IS SO BEAUTIFUL I CANNOT. Every move is so crisp and you can see, they are 13 people and they use it to their advantage quite smartly, especially during the wave formation and the bonfire formation (where other members were lying on the ground and 1 member was standing right in between them; sorry I dunno how to explain it :3) 

This choreo deserves an award istg if they don't get it...this is hands down the best choreo I have seen. This song and the choreo deserves it all 👏👏👏

text: Seventeen are honestly crazy good. They have 13 members, you'd think it would be messy and overcrowded on stage but it's not, they have flawless transitions, every single member moves cleanly and precisely and don't even get me started on the synchronisation. This choreography is a masterpiece, just when I thought Don't Wanna Cry choreo was the peak they make this perfection, when matched with the lyrics you can really feel how emotional and genuine they are. I really adore Seventeen, they are all my role models and I'm always proud of them every single day. One day they will reach the top, I'm 100% certain of that.

author: @skusumadi
text:
i've been a carat for about a year now. when i watch their new music or choreography videos, i'm always moved emotionally. i've watched this dance performance many times already, but today i took a moment to think behind the choreography, behind the lyrics, behind why the song was composed. i actually, legitimately, started to get goosebumps and tear up. it's just so touching because this song was dedicated to us carats, thanking us, when we should really be thanking them.

seventeen's choreography is hands down the best in the pop industry, to me and a lot of other people. it flows so well, and when the performance unit choreographs their dances, they always manage to have a story behind it. the fact that they have 13 members, yet are still so in sync, is just beyond amazing. it just makes me so... moved. i can't even explain with words how much i've started to love them. they've been my ult for quite awhile now, and everytime i always get reminded of why they're my ult when i watch their videos, especially dance ones. once again, thank you seventeen.

author: @irishlajara3658
text:
I don't know why I'm emotional, but I think it's best to say that I feel like this because I truly believe Seventeen has succeeded. Not because of the awards but because they have found people who support their songs and appreciates them for who they are as artists and individual people. I may not know them personally but it's just how it feels for me. Seeing them grow from 2013 until now has truly inspired me in so many ways. I think, maybe for the 3 minutes and 53 seconds I've listened to this song, I have not fan girl and just tried to appreciate what they have prepared for me. For us. 

I write these lengthy comments whenever I see Seventeen, because the passion they have is what I yearn to have in my own career. I want to succeed and likewise, say thank you to the people who have helped me along to way. Thank you is such a common word that we always say whenever we are grateful, but it's still one of the best things to hear from them. I know that Seventeen is a group that I can continue to support until the end, and I am happy to have found that group.

text: Okay, wow. Seventeen has THE most tasteful and artistic choreography in kpop right now. I love how *beautiful* they are? There isn't that toughness and edge I'm used to when a boy group is going hard. Sure it's difficult but it's also just visually stunning and modern and elegant and I just can't stop coming up with descriptors! The emotion in this really sets them apart imho, like that move @ 2:05 when the members on the floor curl into themselves? I almost teared up it's so emotive! Kudos to them, wow

author: @astrochick6171
text: One thing I love (out of many) about Seventeen's dancing is that altough they have 13 members it never looks crowded. It's easy for that to happen with so many people on a stage especially if that stage has limited space. Yet they always look well organized & it's never messy. Hoshi choreographs in such a unique way. He utilizes every member so even when they're not singing or center they still create beautiful formations, even if it's something simple & not only that but it creates a wonderful atmosphere. Our boys are the really special. I've been a carat for close to three years & I'm still amazed at how talented they are. I'm so proud to be a carat bc I'm supporting 13 people who aren't just amazing but strive to become better. Is it humanly possible? I didn't think so but they somehow always come back better than before. I'm so grateful for their hard work & I feel blessed I got to see them transform over the years. I'll continue to support Seventeen. Can't wait to see what they have in store for the future.

author: @themaddy010
text: looking at this from a professional dancers point of view their transitions (the in between moments between the steps) are incredibly clean and smooth. they also have so many different dynamics in their movement - sometimes they're soft, then sharp, then soft again. some other bg's tend to just dance hard and fast which is great, but its truly breathtaking to see svt's change in dynamics. not to mention the use of levels in their choreography - some stand whilst the others are on the floor. i understand its easier to create choreography like this with more dancers and it looks more amazing with more people, but a lot of credit goes to their actual ability. they really make me feel something when i watch them dance, the same way i feel when i watch a professional contemporary dance company or ballet company perform. i dont know who choreographed this but goddamn its truly beautiful

author: @charlottebooker9537
text:
For the New Carats that are just learning their names and want to focus on their favorite member
S.coups - wearing a plaid shirt
Jeonghan -wearing a light jacket and a black face mask 
Joshua - wearing a dark jacket with squares on them, had a face mask but it isn’t over his mouth
Jun - black hoodie, pants and shoes, very exposed stomach 
Hoshi - long white cardigan thing, with a black shirt 
Wonwoo - white hoodie with the hood up, wish we could see his face :,( 
Woozi - the shortest, has a black baseball cap on and a black shirt 
Dk- black hoodie with a rectangle on it 
Mingyu - black shirt and sweatpants, white shoes 
The8- all black with a face mask, his jacket has a pretty sick design on the back 
Seunkwan - black turtle neck, he’s the one that gets lifted up <3 
Vernon - also wearing a baseball cap, he has black sweatpants and a grey shirt with only the top buttons buttoned 
Dino- black hoodie and sweatpants with a strip on the side. 

Hopefully this helps out anyone who can’t tell whos who

author: @aquachan2242
text: I love the uniqueness in every choreo of seventeen. And I've noticed, that in many choreos they use elements of gymnastics, which I rarely find in other kpop choreos. I used to do gymnastics so I know a few elements, and I was surprised to find rather difficult elements in seventeen's choreos. Like there are jumps and turns that we had learned too, and I know how difficult they can be. It really fits seventeen's style of dancing. I just wanted to say that even if they don't do that much acrobatics like other groups, don't underestimate seventeen's choreos. They make difficult things seem easy.

text:
0:44 - 0:48 favorite part 
1:10 *PPEONADIPPEONHANNN*

1:48 that rapid movement 
1:55 - 2:00 favorite part02
2:14 *PPEONADIPPEONHANNN*
2:20 *PPEONADIPPEONHANNN*
2:39 -2:52 The8 nailing his part, me love
3:10 ninjas or smth
3:32 that white thing looking like a flower petal, falling down at the perfect time 

me loves, me appreciates. this shows that seventeen would sweep floors ( 0:25 , 1:01 , 1:45 , 1:48 , 1:54 , 1:55 , 2:05 , 3:26 , 3:31 , 3:35 ) and break necks ( 2:47 ) to make the best choreography. i hope their performance style will go on to become something legendary not only in kpop, but in the whole world. and i noticed that their songs have two faces : the emotional , and the fun ones and i don't think they're planning a song with a sexy face any time soon. and ughhhh choosing the right voice for the right part *PPEONADIPPEONHANNN* 
about the rap, i don't know what makes good rap, but they sound emotional enough to me. 

important question : does anyone else notice cheol's ribcage in some recent pictures? i mean if he's naturally skinny he can do what he likes, but i hope he's not starving himself intentionally or unintentionally. don't stress out too much honnei. work hard, but don't overwork yourself. eat lots, know that you're loved by many no matter what. if there's any problems remember that there'll always be a solution. this goes to every other members too. i hope someone reads this. leaving encouraging messages make me feel anxious. they might never even see this. this is really long. i shouldn't drag it out any further.

author: @louloulemon40
text:
I know that some people like the rock band sound of SVT (like Aju-nice) more than the edm sound of SVT.  But, I really appreciate them for not sticking to a specific genre or style. The rock band sound of SVT may show off their musicality or complexity of the sounds; however, as members have said, edm sounds are great to show off their dance/choreo skills. Given the genre (KPop), it is about both - if not being about so much more.

On that note, Woozi - my boy, Hwaiting!
Hoshi and the choreo team, Hwaiting!
SVT - Hwaiting!
Thank you! Gomapda!

author: @챙-i5t
text:
항상 캐럿 위해 노력해주는 세븐틴 고맙다 :)
힘들텐데 웃으면서 팬들과 소통해주는 세븐틴 고맙다 :)

리더여서 부담감이 클텐데 웃어주는 승철오빠 고맙다 
윤엄마라는 별명으로 세븐틴 챙겨주는 정한오빠 고맙다
뒤에서 묵묵히 세븐틴 멤버들 챙겨주는 지수오빠 고맙다
타지에서 와서 힘들텐데 노력해주는 준휘오빠 고맙다
춤 창작하는거 어려울텐데 춤 만들어서 보여주는 순영오빠 고맙다
원우개그로 팬들과 세븐틴 분위기 띄어주는 원우오빠 고맙다
프로듀싱,작곡 등 여러가지 힘들텐데 완성도 높은 노래로 찾아와주는 지훈오빠 고맙다
허리부상으로 외로움 많이 탔을텐데 견뎌준 명호오빠 고맙다
여러 예능 출연해서 캐럿 미소짓게해주는 민규오빠 고맙다
메보라 목 아플텐데 시원한 고음 , 쭉쭉 올려주는 석민오빠 고맙다
밝게 웃어주고 세븐틴의 비타민으로 노력해주는 승관오빠 고맙다
래퍼에서 보컬로 성장하여 노래 불러주려 노력하는 한솔오빠 고맙다
막내라서 치이고 힘들테지만 웃어주는 찬오빠 고맙다

응원법 크게 해주시는 캐럿들 고맙다
이쁜 말투로 세븐틴 웃게해주는 캐럿들 고맙다
세븐틴 영상에 찾아가주는 캐럿들 고맙다 

" 뻔하디 뻔한 이 말을 내가 이제서야 꺼내보지만 ••• "

" 고맙다 고맙다 또 고맙다 뿐이지만 ••• " 

세븐틴 아끼고 예쁘고 고맙다
캐럿들 아끼고 예쁘고 고맙다

고맙다라는 말이 쉬운 말은 아니지만 , 고맙다라는 말이
무의식적으로 튀어나오지만 , 고맙다라는 말이 누구에겐
힘이 되지만 , 고맙다라는 말이 누구에겐 생소하지만 

고맙다 라는 말을 한번쯤 전해봅시다 , 고맙다 ♡
